      {
        "id": "a9c53f978a61353d355e476dfbb6eed61b797109",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1077,
          "name": "Michael O'Brien",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "frank.obrien@amdocs.com",
          "username": "michaelobrien"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 11:33:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI am worried that the startup times are a bit arbitrary - if the pod comes up on a very slow file system, or during even more contention with other pods etc.. seems like the real issue is the fact that a deleted/restarted pod reuses the file system - It would be good if the DB was cleared on every restart of the pod - or the db startup would recognize the diff from the last partial write",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "19aa57aa0df7757d7544dee5d658d784c76d2356",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 14:59:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOn my local environment, the DB initialization took about 3.5 minutes.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "8c5927729c8698a9b3bf5a6d3ae4267d871a08d8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 67,
          "name": "Hector Anapan-Lavalle",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ha076r@att.com",
          "username": "ha076r"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 16:24:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "c2d187ff035db03827f82afa44def81c1ea62e6c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 131,
          "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
          "username": "mkhinda"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 17:51:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nThis is a workaround that can be applied in the end users own values file and IMO doesn't need to be checked in or it will become \"the solution\" and other charts will have some precedence to apply the same band-aid. \n\nI would prefer a better solution that detects the true startup of the database and its schema.  I added a comment to the JIRA with more info and logs.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "6e9cc82094bb98f3ad557a2f31debba237438fe5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 131,
          "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
          "username": "mkhinda"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 18:09:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOn second thought, in the interest of time I would be okay with increasing the default from 10s to something higher, just not 10 minutes.  In my envs, I haven't seen it take that long to load.  We've done 90 seconds in other places as a new default.  How about 3-5 minutes?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a7d376c581147f8011a9d59e09fb2da24047dda2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 18:09:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI agree on the \"right\" solution.  However...\n\nGiven that it's nearly impossible for the DB to complete initialization in 10 seconds, should we not at least bump the default liveness initial delay up to a value that has a chance to work?\n\nOtherwise we're delivering OOM with out-of-the-box corrupted portal databases and a Portal UI container that cannot start, and then have to train people on how and why they have to manually override and recover from an unusable default setting.\n\nUnless someone can implement the \"right\" solution by RC2, which is tomorrow.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "b0aac501bd38445aaaab083c8decfbb645517452",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 35,
          "name": "Gary Wu",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gary.wu@gmail.com",
          "username": "gwu"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 18:15:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n5 minutes is probably sufficient in most cases.  Will submit a new patchset shortly.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
